    "actions_taken": [
      "Pressure was bled down to repair the check valve",
      "Injured employee was transported to a medical facility",
      "Onsite investigation conducted on 14-OCT-2014"
    ],
    "summary": "On October 13, 2014 at approximately 1335 hours, an employee was injured while attempting to hydro test a pipeline on a new facility. As the crew began to unscrew cap screws to access a leaking check valve, trapped pressure downstream of check valve 1 (CV1) was released, striking the injured employee in the left side of face and head, rendering him unconscious. The incident resulted from failure to check the gauge downstream of CV1 and inadequate supervision of hydro-testing operations.",
